verses.english:
Glory be to Him who lov'd us,
Wash'd us from each spot and stain;
Made us kings with Him to reign;
Glory, Glory,
To the lamb that once was slain!

verses.yoruba:
Ogo fun Ẹni t'o fẹ wa,
T'o wẹ abawọn wa nu;
Ogo fun Ẹni  t'o ra wa,
T'o mu wa ba On j'Ọba;
Ogo, Ogo
Fun Ọd'agutan t'a pa.

verses.english:
We are never, never weary of the grand old song;
Glory to God, Hallelujah;
We can sing it loud as ever with our faith more strong,
Glory to God, Hallelujah.

Thou art a post protected,
From storms that round us rise;
A garden intersected with steams of paradise;
Thou are a cooling fountain,
In life's dry dreary sand;
From Thee, like Pisgah's mountain,
We view our promised land.

Praise Him for redemption, free to every soul;
Praise Him for the fountain that can make us whole;
For His gifts of kindness and His loving care,
For the blest assurance that He answers prayer.

verses.yoruba:
Yin Ọlọrun Abra'am,
Nip'asẹ Ẹni ti
Mo dide, mo si wa 'tunu lọwọ 'tun Rẹ;
Mo kọ aye silẹ;
Ọgbọn at'ọla rẹ;
On nikan si ni ipin mi,
At'asa mi.

verses.english:
Jesus the name that charms our fears,
That bids our sorrows cease;
'Tis music in the sinner's ears;
'Tis life, and health, and peace.

He breaks the pow'r of cancel'd sin,
And sets the prisoner free;
His blood can make the foulest clean;
His blood avail'd for me.

O worship the King, all glorious above;
O gratefully sing, His pow'r and His love;
Our shield and defender, the ancient of days;
Pavilion'd in splendour, and girded with praise.

Alleluia, song of sweetness,
Voice of joy that cannot die;
Alleluia is the anthem,
Ever dear to choirs on high;
In the house of God abiding,
Thus they sing eternally.

verses.yoruba:
Aleluya! Orin t'o dun,
Ohun ayọ ti ki ku;
Aleluya! Orin didun,
T'awọn t'o wa l'ọrun fẹ;
N'ile ti Ọlorun mi ngbe,
Ni wọn nkọ tọsan toru.

verses.english:
Alleluia may not always
Be our song while here below;
Alleluia, our transgressions,
Make us for a while forego;
For the solemn time is coming,
When our tears for sin must flow.

Father-like He tends and spares us;
Well our feeble frame he knows,
In His hands He gently bears us,
Rescues us from all our foes;
Praise Him! Praise Him!
Widely as His mercy flows.

Praise the Lord ye heaven bow down;
Praise Him all ye saints above;
Let the sun and moon rejoice;
Let the stars praise Him, praise Him!

verses.yoruba:
Yin Oluwa ọrun wolẹ;
Yin ẹyin mimọ loke,
K'orun at'osupa ko yọ;
K'awọn 'rawọ fiyin fun.

Yin Oluwa o ti sọrọ;
Awọn aye gbohun Rẹ;
Fun wọn o fi ofin lelẹ;
Ta ko le bajẹ titi.

verses.english:
Praise Him He has authority;
His promise can never fail;
Through His power He made His people,
To overcome sin and death.

verses.yoruba:
Yin nitori ti o lọla;
Ileri Rẹ ko le yẹ;
O ti mu awọn eyan Rẹ;
Bori iku oun ẹsẹ.

verses.english:
Praise the Lord who's our salvation;
Host of heavens hear Him speak;
Heaven earth and all creatures;
Praise Him and lift up His name.

verses.yoruba:
Yin Oluwa igbala wa;
Ogun ọrun sọ'pa Rẹ;
Ọrun aye gbogbo ẹda;
Yin, kẹ gb'orukọ Rẹ ga.

verses.english:
Praise to the Lord, who o'er all things so wondrously reigneth,
Shelters thee under His wings, yea, so gently sustaineth;
Hast thou not seen?
All that is needful hath been;
Granted in what he ordaineth.

verses.yoruba:
Ẹnit'o pasẹ fun 'lẹ
Lati mu eso pọ si;
Anu Rẹ, o wa titi;
L'ododo dajudaju.

Baba Ẹlẹda wa,
af'ifẹ gbadura;
Ẹni t'O fun wa ni
Ọna, otọ, iye;
Fi anu rọ 'jo 'bukun Rẹ
S'ori awa ti njọsin yi.

Baba Ẹlẹda wa,
A s'ọkan wa paya;
Ọkan ominira wa,
Nyin Ọ lọpọlọpọ;
Mi imisi Rẹ s'okan wa,
K'orin 'yin wale bu jade.

Fun anu t'o pọ bi yanrin,
Ti mo naba lojumọ;
Lat'ọdọ Jesu Oluwa;
Ki l'emi o fi fun?

verses.english:
The Lord, ye know, is God indeed;
Without our aid He did us make,
We are His folk, He doth us feed;
And for His sheep he doth us take.

verses.yoruba:
Oluwa, On ni Ọlọrun,
Laisi 'ranwọ wa O da wa;
Agbo Rẹ ni wa, O mbọ wa;
O si fi wa s'agutan Rẹ.

verses.english:
O enter then His gates with praise;
Approach with joy His courts unto;
Praise, laud, and bless His name always,
For it is seemly so to do.

For why? The Lord our God is good;
His mercy is for ever sure;
His truth at all times firmly stood,
And shall from age to age endure.

Hallowed Day and Holy,
Thou holy day of rest;
We ought to give one full day,
To God, the good and kind;
Other days bring the tear drops,
Thou wipes the tears away;
Thou art a day of gladness,
I love thy happy morn.

verses.yoruba:
Ọsẹ, Ọsẹ rere,
Iwọ ọjọ simi;
O yẹ k'a fi ọjọ kan,
Fun Ọlọrun rere;
B'ọjọ mi ba m'ẹkun wa,
Iwọ n'oju wa nu;
Iwọ ti s'ọjọ ayọ,
Emi fẹ dide rẹ.

verses.english:
Hallowed Day and Holy,
There's no work today;
We will suspend our labour,
Until tomorrow's day;
How beautiful and how bright,
How blessed day of rest;
Other days speak of troubles,
But thou give hope of rest.

verses.yoruba:
Ọsẹ, Ọsẹ rere,
A k'yo sisẹ loni;
A o f'isẹ wa gbogbo,
Fun aisimi ọla;
Didan l'oju rẹ ma dan,
'Wo, arẹwa ọjọ;
Ọjọ mi nso ti lala,
Iwọ nsọ ti 'simi.

verses.english:
Hallowed Day and Holy,
Thy hour delights me so;
A taste of heav'n you give us,
Like that eternal rest;
Lord, let me be partaker,
Of rest beyond the grave;
To sing and serve Thee ever,
With all Thy saints above.

verses.yoruba:
Ọsẹ, Ọsẹ rere,
Ọsẹ, Ọsẹ rere,
Wakati rẹ wu mi;
Ọjọ ọrun ni 'wọ se,
'Wọ apẹrẹ ọrun;
Oluwa, jẹ ki njogun,
'Simi lẹyin iku;
Kin le ma sin Ọ titi,
Pẹlu eniyan Rẹ.

verses.english:
Then will I tell the sinners round,
Blessed be the name of the Lord;
What a dear Saviour I have found;
Blessed be the name of the Lord.

verses.yoruba:
Ọba ogo, alafia,
Uno fẹran Rẹ;
Ifẹ na ki y'o dẹkun,
Uno sunmọ Ọ;
N'tori Ọ ti gbẹbẹ mi,
O ti gb'ohun mi;
O ka iwe aya mi,
O da mi n'de.

Iyin lo yẹ Kristi Ọba;
Ẹ de l'ade pupọ;
Ẹni t'O fi ifẹ,
'Mọlẹ at'ẹmi Rẹ,
Mu 'rapada wa s'aye;
Iyin, ọla at'ogo f'Oluwa.

B'irun mi jẹ kiki ahọn,
Ko to fun iyin Rẹ;
B'Ọlọrun tilẹ ga
Ju gbogbo yin lo,
Sibẹ un o kọrin ọpẹ;
Iyin, ọla at'ogo f'Oluwa.

Ta ni ko ni bẹru Rẹ;
Ti ko ni yin Ọ logo?
Iwọ nikan lo jẹ mimọ;
Gbogbo agbaye ni yo yin Ọ.

verses.english:
The home of God is within mankind
He will live with them;
They shall be His people;
And God, Himself shall be with them.

verses.yoruba:
Ile Ọlọrun pẹl' eyan;
Yi o ba wọn gbe;
Won yi o jẹ eniyan Rẹ;
Oun o si wa pẹlu wọn.

verses.english:
God shall wipe away all tears;
And there shall be no more death;
Neither sorrow nor crying;
Neither there be any more pain.

verses.yoruba:
Yo nu omije gbogbo nu;
Ki yo si iku mọ;
Tabi ọfọ tabi ekun;
Bẹni ki yo si 'rora mọ.

verses.english:
Amen blessing and glory;
Wisdom thanks giving honour,
Power and Might be unto our God;
Forever and ever.

verses.yoruba:
Amin ibukun at'ogo;
Ọgbọn ọpẹ ati ọla;
Agbara ipa fun Ọlọrun wa;
Lae ati lae.

verses.english:
All things bright and beautiful;
All creatures great and small;
All things wise and wonderful;
The Lord God made them all.

verses.yoruba:
Ohun didan to lẹwa;
Loke ati nilẹ;
Gbogbo ohun iyanu;
Oluwa lo da wọn.

verses.english:
Each little flower that opens;
Each little bird that sings;
He made their glowing colours;
He made their tiny wings.

verses.yoruba:
Gbogbo itanna ti ntan;
At'ẹyẹ ti nkọrin;
Ọwọ Rẹ lo fi dawọn;
At'ọrọ Rẹ pẹlu.

verses.english:
The purple-headed mountain;
The river running by;
The sunset and the morning;
That brightens up the sky.

verses.yoruba:
Oke giga ti a nri;
Gbogbo awọn odo;
Riran orun wiwọ rẹ;
Nipa asẹ Rẹ ni.

verses.english:
The cold wind in the winter;
The pleasant summer sun;
The fruit in the garden;
He made them every one;

verses.yoruba:
Ọtọ ni igba erun;
Ati igba ojo;
Awọn eso ti nso;
Oun ni o da wọn.

verses.english:
He gave us eyes to see them;
And lips that we might tell;
How great is God Almighty;
Who has made all things well.

verses.yoruba:
Oju ta fi nriran;
Ẹnu ta fi nsọrọ;
Ọlọrun Alagbara;
Sohun gbogbo dara.

verses.english:
God the Lord is King of Glory,
Zion, tell the world His fame;
Ancient Israel, the story tell
Of His faithfulness proclaim;
He is Holy;
Holy is His awful name.

In old times when dangers darkened,
When, invoked by priest and seer;
To His people's cry He hearkened,
Answer'd them in all their fear;
He is Holy;
As they call'd, they found Him near.

Laws divine to them were spoken
From the pillar of the cloud;
Sacred precepts, quickly broken!
Fiercely then His vengeance flow'd
He is Holy;
To the dust their hearts were bowed.

verses.yoruba:
Awọn l'afun l'ofin mimọ
Lat' inu awọsanma;
Ilana mimọ ti wọn ru,
Mu ki O binu si won!
Ẹni Mimọ;
Wọn kanu fun ẹsẹ wọn.

verses.english:
God in Christ is all forgiving,
Waits His promise to fulfil,
Come, exalt Him all the living;
Come, ascend His Holy hill!
He is Holy;
Worship at His Holy hill.

verses.yoruba:
Ile iyawo na kun fun ase;
Wọle, wọle tọ ọkọ 'yawo lọ;
Wọle, wọle, wọle nisisiyi.

chorus.english:
O hallelujah, yes 'tis heav'n Tis heav'n to know my sins forgiv'n;
On land or sea, what matters where?
Where Jesus is, 'tis heaven there.

verses.english:
Go, labour on, while it is day;
The world's dark night is hastening on:
Speed, speed thy work, cast sloth away;
It is not thus that souls are won.

Toil on, faint not, keep watch, and pray;
Be wise, the erring soul to win;
Go forth into the world's highway,
Compel the wanderer to come in.

verses.yoruba:
Ma sisẹ lọ, ma yọ pẹlu,
Lẹhin isẹ 'wọ o simi;
O fẹrẹ gb'ohun Jesu na;
Y'O ke tantan pe, 'Emi de'.

Gbọ! Orin ti Jubeli,
O dabi sisan ara;
Tabi bi kikun okun,
'Gbat' igbi rẹ ba nlu 'lẹ;
Aleluya! Ọlọrun
Olodumare jọba;
Aleluya! k'ọrọ na
Dun yi gbogbo aye ka.

Yo jọba yi aye ka,
Pẹlu agbara nlanla;
Yo jọba 'gbati ọrun
At'aye ba kọja lọ;
Opin de; lab'ọpa Rẹ
L'ọta eniyan subu;
Aleluya! Ọlọrun
Ni gbogbo l'ohun gbogbo.

verses.english:
Blessings abound where'er He reign,
The prisoner leaps to lose his chains;
The weary find eternal rest;
And all the sons of want are blest.

Arise, take Thy lamp light it
Wear thy holy garment;
Prepare thyself to meet Him
For He shall soon arrive;
Lord, how long will thou tarry
Till thou cometh again?
That we may not get tired;
Till we shall meet with Thee.

Rejoice, for Jesus reigns,
Enthroned in human hearts;
He breaks the prison chains,
And makes them free indeed;
The devil might God's child oppose
No fear of foe, God's word goes on.

The work of righteousness,
Tidings of truth and peace;
For comfort in our life
Shall spread all round about;
Gentiles and Jews shall all bow down,
And will worship acceptably.

There's pow'r with Thee for the
Protection of Thine own;
And to Thy high decree
Shall millions take heed to;
The heav'ns rejoice to see Thy work,
The Islands far hear Thy command.

This perfect heav'nly seed
Shall grow to a big tree;
Like the blessed leaven
Shall spread all o'er the earth;
Till God the Son comes back again
It will go on, Amen, Amen.

verses.yoruba:
Irugbin t'ọrun yi,
O fẹrẹ d'igi nla;
Abukun wukara
Ko le saitan kiri;
Tit'Ọlọrun Ọmọ tun wa
Ko le sai lọ, Amin, Amin.

Ohun t'a fi fun Ọ
Tirẹ ni, Oluwa;
Gbogbo hun ti a si ni;
Ọwọ Rẹ l'o tiwa.

verses.english:
Tell it out among the heathen that the Lord is king;
Tell it out, Tell it out:
Tell it out among the nations, let them shout and sing;
Tell it out, tell it out:
Tell it out with adoration that He shall increase,
That the mighty King of Glory is the King of peace;
Tell it out with jubilation, though the waves may roar,
That He sitteth on the water floods, our King for evermore.

Tell it out among the heathen that the Saviour reigns;
Tell it out Tell it out:
Tell it out among the nations, bid them burst their chains;
Tell it out Tell it out:
Tell it out among the weeping ones that Jesus lives;
Tell it out among the weary ones what rest He gives;
Tell it out among the sinful that He came to save;
Tell it out among the dying that
He triumphed o'er the grave.

Tell it out among the heathen that Jesus reigns above;
Tell it out Tell it out:
Tell it out among the nations that His reigns is love;
Tell it out Tell it out:
Tell it out among the highways and the lanes at home;
Let it ring across the mountains and the ocean foam!
Like the sound of many waters, let our glad shout be,
Till it echo and re-echo from the Islands of the sea.

The mighty Kings of kings with healing in His wings;
To every captive soul; a full deliverance brings;
And through the vacant cells; the song of triumph rings;
The comforter has come!

Oh, boundless love divine; how shall this tongue of mine;
To wandering mortals tell; the matchless grace divine;
That I may with Him dwell; and in His image shine;
The comforter has come!

Oh, let the echoes fly; above the vaulted sky;
And all the saints above; to all below reply;
In strain of endless love; the song that ne'er will die;
The comforter has come.

chorus.english:
The Comforter has come!
The Comforter has come!
The Holy Ghost from heaven;
The Father's promise given;
Oh spread the tidings round;
Wherever man is found;
The comforter has come.

verses.english:
Nothing in my hands I bring,
Simply to Thy cross I cling;
Naked, come to Thee for dress;
Helpless, look to Thee for grace;
Foul, I to the fountain fly;
Wash me, Savior, or I die.

verses.yoruba:
Ko s'ohun ti mo mu wa,
Mo rọ̀ mọ agbelebu;
Mo wa k'o d'asọ̀ bo mi,
Mo nwo Ọ fún iranwọ;
Mo wà si b'orisun ní,
Wẹ mí, Olugbala mí.

verses.english:
Guide me, O Thou great Jehovah,
Pilgrim through this barren land
I am weak, but Thou art mighty;
Hold me with Thy pow'rful hand;
Bread of heaven! Bread of heaven!
Feed me now and evermore.

verses.yoruba:
S'ilẹkun isun ogo ni,
Orisun im'arale;
Jẹ ki imọlẹ Rẹ ọrun
Se amọna mi jalẹ;
Olugbala, Olugbala,
S'agbara at'asa mi.

verses.english:
Hark, my soul! It is the Lord;
'Tis thy Saviour, hear His word;
Jesus speaks, and speaks to thee:
Say, poor sinner, lov'st thou Me?

I delivered thee when bound,
And, when bleeding, healed thy wound;
Sought thee wand'ring, set thee right;
Turned thy darkness into light.

Thou shalt see my glory soon.
When the work of grace is done;
Partner of My throne shalt be;
Say, poor sinner, lov'st thou Me?

Lord, it is my chief complaint
That may love is weak and faint;
Yet I love Thee, and adore;
O for grace to love Thee more!

Saviour, breathe forgiveness o'er us;
All our weakness Thou dost know;
Thou didst tread this earth before us,
Thou didst feel its keenest woe;
Lone and dready; faint and weary,
Through the desert Thou didst go.

I need Thee every hour;
Stay Thou near by;
Temptations lose their pow'r
When Thou art nigh.

chorus.english:
I need Thee, O I need Thee,
Every hour I need Thee;
O bless me now, my Saviour;
I come to Thee.

verses.yoruba:
Mo f'ọjọ aye mi
Se wahala fun ọ,
Ki iwọ ba le mọ,
Adun ayeraye;
Mo l'ọpọ' dun fun Ọ;
O lo 'kan fun mi bi?

Ile ti Baba mi,
At'itẹ ogo mi,
Mo fi silẹ w'aye,
Mo d'alarinkiri;
Mo fi'lẹ 'tori rẹ;
Ki l'o fi'lẹ fun mi?

Mo jiya pọ fun ọ,
Ti ẹnu ko le so,
Mo jijakadi nla,
'Tori igbala rẹ;
Mo jiya po fun ọ;
O le jiya fun mi?

Fi ara rẹ fun Mi,
Fi aye rẹ fun Mi,
Diju si nkan t'aye,
Si wo hun t'ọrun;
Mo f'ara mi fun ọ;
Si fara rẹ fun Mi.

Mo l'Ọrẹ kan ifẹ Rẹ pọ!
O fẹ mi k'emi to m'Ọ;
Okun ifẹ l'O fi fa mi,
O si demi mọ 'ra Rẹ;
Koko 'fe Rẹ t'a ko le tu,
Lo mọ ọkan mi sibe;
Mo jẹ Tirẹ, On jẹ temi,
Lae ati titi laelae.

verses.english:
Ev'n on earth, as though a glass,
Darkly, let Thy glory pass;
Make forgiveness feel so sweet,
Make Thy Spirit's help so meet;
Ev'n on earth, Lord, make me know
Something of how much I owe.

Christians, awake, salute the happy morn,
Whereon the Saviour of the world was born;
Rise to adore the mystery of love,
Which hosts of angels chanted from above;
With them the joyful tidings first begun,
Of God incarnate and the Virgin's Son.

verses.yoruba:
Ji, 'wọ Kristian, k'o ki orọ ayọ
Ti a bi Olugbala araye;
Dide, k'o kọrin ifẹ Ọlọrun
T'awọn Angẹli nkọ n'ijọ kini;
Lat' ọdọ wọn n'ihin na ti bẹrẹ;
Ihin Ọm'Ọlọrun t'a bi s'aye.

verses.english:
O may we keep and ponder in our mind
God's wondrous love in saving lost mankind;
Trace we the Babe, who hath retrieved our loss,
From the poor manger to the bitter Cross;
Tread in His steps, assisted by His grace,
Till man's first heav'nly state again takes place.

verses.yoruba:
Nigbana 'gba 'ba de ọrun lọhun
A o kọrin ayo t'irapada;
Ogo Ẹni t'a bi fun wa loni,
Y'o ma ran yi wa ka titi laelae;
A o ma kọrin ifẹ Rẹ titi,
Ọba angẹli, Ọba eniyan.

verses.english:
O beautiful star of Bethlehem,
Shining afar through shadows dim;
Giving the light for those who long have gone;
Guiding the wise men on their way,
Unto the place where Jesus lay;
O beautiful star of Bethlehem, shine on

verses.yoruba:
Irawọ didan ti Bẹtlẹhẹm,
To ntan s'ọna okunkun wa;
Tan 'mọlẹ na f'awọn to ti sako;
To si nto awọn amoye,
Sibi ti a bi Jesu si;
Irawọ didan ti Betlehem, maa tan.

Irawọ didan ireti wa
To tan 'mọlẹ s'okunkun wa;
Lori oke titi di ojumọ,
To nmuwa wọ 'nu ilu na,
Ti imọlẹ ọjọ rere;
Irawọ didan ti Betlehem, maa tan.

verses.english:
O beautiful star the hope of grace,
For the redeemed the good and the blessed;
Yonder in glory when the crown is won,
Jesus is now the star divine;
Brighter, and brighter He will shine on,
O beautiful star of Bethlehem, shine on

verses.yoruba:
Irawọ didan ti Bẹtlẹhẹm,
Fun awọn t'ati ra pada;
Ti wọn yo si gba ade ologo;
Jesu ni irawọ didan,
Yo si ma tan titi aye;
Irawọ didan ti Betlehem, maa tan.

verses.english:
Joy to the earth! The Saviour reigns;
Let men their songs employ;
While fields and floods, rocks, hills and plains,
Repeat the sounding joy.

chorus.english:
Rejoice, rejoice! The incarnate Word,
Has come on earth to dwell;
No sweeter sound than this is Heard-Emmanuel.

verses.yoruba:
O t'ọrun wa s'ode aye,
On l'Ọlọrun Oluwa;
O f'ile ẹran se ile
'Bujẹ ẹran fun 'busun;
Lọdọ awọn otosi,
Ni Jesu be li aye.

verses.english:
For He is our childhood's pattern;
Day by day like us He grew;
He was little, weak, and helpless;
Tears and smiles like us He knew
And He feeleth for our sadness,
And He shareth in our gladness.

verses.yoruba:
'Tori On je awose wa,
A ma dagba bi awa;
O kere ko le da nkan se,
A ma sọkun bi awa;
O si le ba wa daro,
O le bawa yo pẹlu.

verses.english:
And our eyes at last shall see Him,
Through His own redeeming love;
For that child so dear and gentle
Is our Lord in heaven above;
And He leads His children on
To the place where He is gone.

verses.yoruba:
A o f'oju wa ri nikehin
Ni agbara ifẹ Rẹ;
Nitori ọmọ rere yi
Ni Oluwa wa l'ọrun;
O nto awa ọmọ Rẹ
S'ọna ibiti On lọ.

verses.english:
Command Thy blessing, Jesus,Lord,
May we Thy true disciples be;
Speak to each heart the mighty word;
Say to the weakest, follow Me.

At evening time when sun goes down;
Sick people are brought before Him
So many are their afflictions;
They went home with joy and gladness.

verses.yoruba:
Lọjọ alẹ gba t'orun wọ;
Wọn gbe abirun wọdọ Rẹ;
Oniruuru ni aisan wọn;
Sugbọn wọn fayọ lọ'le wọn.

Jesu a de lọj'alẹ yi;
A sun mọ tawa tarun wa;
Bi a ko tilẹ le ri Ọ;
Sugbọn a mọ po sun mọ wa.

verses.english:
Saviour, help us in our misery;
Many are sick and unhappy;
Many have not your love at heart;
Many are lukewarm in their heart.

verses.yoruba:
Olugbala wo osi wa;
O mi kosan, 'mi 'banujẹ;
O mi ko ni ifẹ si Ọ;
Ifẹ ẹlomiran tutu.

verses.english:
Some know the world is vanity;
Still they pursue the lust of world;
Many make friendship with the world;
The best of friend they make you not;

The lord Jesus our dear Saviour;
You come just like as we are now;
Trials, temptations you passed through;
Our weaknesses are all known to you.

verses.yoruba:
Sugbọn Jesu Olugbala;
Ẹni bi awa ni'wọse;
'Wọ tiri 'danwo bi awa;
'Wọ si ti mọ ailera wa.

Mo t'ibi ẹru bẹrẹ;
Gba mi ni ẹru ẹsẹ;
Ki ẹjẹ tO 'ta silẹ,
Wẹ ẹbi ọkan mi nu.

verses.english:
Here I raise my Ebenezer;
Hither by Thine help I'm come;
And I hope, by Thy good pleasure,
Safely to arrive at home,
Jesus sought me when a stranger,
Wand'ring from the fold of God;
He, to rescue me from danger,
Interpos'd His precious blood.

Lord, dismiss us with Thy blessing,
Fill our hearts with joy and peace;
Let us each, Thy love possessing
Triumph in redeeming grace;
Oh refresh us, oh refresh us,
Traveling through this wilderness.

Lord, I hear of showers of blessing
Thou art scattering, full and free;
Showers, the thirsty land refreshing;
Let some drops now fall on me.

Pass me not, O tender Saviour;
Let me love and cling to Thee;
I am longing for Thy favour;
Whilst Thou'rt calling, O call me.

I must tell Jesus all of my trials;
I cannot bear these burdens alone,
In my distress He kindly will help me;
He ever loves and cares for His own.

verses.yoruba:
N'sọ fun Jesu! Gbogbo 'damu mi'
Alaanu, oloore ọfẹ ni;
Ti mo ba sọ fun, yo ran mi lọwọ;
Yo mopin de ba isoro mi.

Aye tan mi jẹ, o fẹ fa mi lọ;
Idanwo fẹ bori ọkan mi;
N'sọ fun Jesu! Yo ran mi lọwọ,
Yo fun mi nisẹgun nin' aye.

Ibi kan wa fun idapọ;
Nibi ọrẹ npade ọrẹ;
L'airi 'ra nipa igbagbọ,
Nwọn y'itẹ-anu kanna ka.

Fun mi ni igbagbọ;
At'ireti;
Fun mi l'ayo 'gbala
Ninu Jesu;
F'emi iye fun mi,
Fun mi l'ade ogo,
'Gba ti mo ba jinde
Ki njọ Jesu.

verses.english:
In the blood of Jesus;
My sins are washed away;
For the stains to remove;
Christ blood is enough for me.

verses.yoruba:
Ninu ẹjẹ Jesu,
La we ẹsẹ mi nu;
Fun gbogbo abawọn;
Ẹjẹ naa to fun mi.

verses.english:
Every time every were;
The Lord sends His blessings,
For more power of your power;
I will be asking for.

verses.yoruba:
'Jojumọ 'gbakugba;
Lo nan 'bukun si mi;
Fun ẹkun agbara;
Ni n'o ma beere si.

verses.english:
I want to close to Him;
And follow Him daily,
My desire He will meet;
When asked with faith in God.

verses.yoruba:
Mo fẹ sun mọ Jesu;
Ki ntẹle lọjọjọ;
Yo fifẹ mi fun mi;
Ki nbeere ni gbagbọ.

verses.english:
I do have peace of God;
In this world so sinful;
I continue to pray;
That I may be made whole.

verses.yoruba:
Mo ni Alafia;
Lat' aye ẹsẹ yi;
N'o si ma gbadura;
Ki nle di mimọ lau.

chorus.english:
I will wash in the blood;
In the blood of Jesus,
I will wash in the blood;
In the blood so precious.

chorus.yoruba:
N'o tun wẹ nin'ẹjẹ;
Ninu ẹjẹ Jesu;
N'o tun wẹ nin'ẹjẹ;
Ninu ẹjẹ 'yebiye.

verses.yoruba:
Oluwa 'Wọ wa nitosi,
N'apa Rẹ, de 'ti Rẹ silẹ;
Si ọrun, sọkale kankan;
Se gbogbo ọkan ni Tirẹ.

verses.english:
No words can tell what blest relief,
There for my every want I find;
What strength for warfare, balm for grief;
What peace of mind.

verses.yoruba:
Ma gbadura;
Ẹmi mbẹbẹ, n'nu rẹ,
Fun gbogbo aini rẹ igba-gbogbo

Ma gbadura;
L'abẹ ẹru ẹsẹ,
Adura nri ẹjẹ Jesu ti nsan.

Ma gbadura;
B'are tilẹ mu ọ,
Adura ngbe wa s'ẹba 'tẹ Baba.

Ma gbadura;
N'nu wahala aye,
Adura l'o fun ọkan n'isimi,

Ma gbadura;
B'ayọ ba yi ọ ka,
Adura nlu harp o nkọrin angẹl'

Ma gbadura;
B'awọn to fẹran ku,
Adura mba wọn mu omi iye.

verses.english:
That eye is fix'd on seraph throngs;
That arm upholds the sky;
That ear is fill'd with angel songs:
That love is throned on high.

Early let us seek Thy favour;
Early let us do Thy will;
Blessed Lord and only Saviour,
With Thy love our bosoms fill;
Blessed Jesus, Blessed Jesus,
Thou hast loved us, love us still,
Blessed Jesus, Blessed Jesus,
Thou hast loved us, love us still.

verses.yoruba:
Wakati adura didun!
T'o gbe mi lọ kuro l'aye,
Lọ 'waju itẹ Baba mi,
Ki nsọ gbogbo ẹdun mi fun;
Nigba 'banujẹ at' aro
Adua l'abo fun ọkan mi;
Emi si bọ lọwọ esu;
'Gbati mo ba gb'adua didun.

chorus.yoruba:
Sọ wọn fun Jesu,
Sọ wọn fun Jesu,
Sọ wọn fun Jesu, On y'o gbọ;
Sa gbẹkẹle ki O si gba A gbọ;
On yio si tu ọ ninu.

verses.yoruba:
Idanwo ha wa fun wa bi? 
A ha ni wahala bi?
A ko gbọdọ sọ 'reti nu;
Sa gbadura s'Oluwa.
Ko s'olotọ ọrẹ bi Rẹ;
Ti o le ba wa daro,
Jesu ti mọ ailera wa;
Sa gbadura s'Oluwa.

verses.english:
Through each perplexing path of life
Our wand'ring footsteps guide;
Give us each day our daily bread;
And raiment fit provide.

From death unto life He hath brought us
And made us by grace Sons of God;
A fountain is opened for sinners;
Oh, wash and be cleans'd in the blood.

Accept now God's offer of mercy;
To Jesus, oh, hasten today;
For He will received him that cometh,
And never will turn him away.

verses.yoruba:
Ani idapọ to dun pupọ,nTẹnu ko le sọ rara,
Ayọ la lati gbe ninu Rẹ;
A! Inu mi dun.

verses.english:
Thy promise is my only plea;
With this I venture nigh;
Thou callest burden'd souls to Thee
And each, O Lord am I.

verses.yoruba:
Bi mo ti ri 'Wọ o gba mi,
'Wọ o gba mi, t'ọwọ t'ẹsẹ;
'Tori mo gba 'leri Rẹ gbọ;
Olugbala, mo de.

Bi mo ti ri, n'nu fẹ nla ni
T'o fi titobi Rẹ han mi;
Nihin yi ati ni oke;
Olugbala, mo de.

Lati 'nu ide ibanujẹ,
Jesu mo de, Jesu mo de,
Mo wa gba ominira at'ayọ,
Jesu mo wa 'dọ Rẹ,
Alaisan, emi nfẹ iwosan;
Alaini, sọ mi di ọlọrọ;
Ẹlẹsẹ, mo wa si ọdọ Rẹ;
Jesu, mo wa 'dọ Rẹ.

verses.english:
Pity, and heal my sin-sick soul;
'Tis Thou alone canst make me whole;
Fallen, till' me Thine image shine,
And cursed I am, till Thou art mine.

verses.yoruba:
Fi anu wo ọkan mi san;
'Wọ l'o le se awotan mi;
Mo ti subu, mo si segbe,
K'aworan Rẹ to tan n'nu mi.

verses.english:
At last I own it cannot be
That I should it myself for Thee;
Here then to Thee I all resign;
Thine is the work and only Thine.

verses.yoruba:
Oluwa, sanu, dariji;
Da ọkan t'o yipada si;
Ki se pe anu Rẹ tobi
Ẹlẹsẹ ko le rọ mọ Ọ?

verses.english:
Sinful, sighing to be blest,
Bound, and longing to be free;
Weary, waiting for my rest;
God be merciful to me.

verses.yoruba:
Irobinujẹ ọkan!
Nko gbodo gb'oju s'oke;
Iwo sa mo ẹdun mi;
'Ọlọrun, sanu fun mi'.

verses.english:
From this sinful heart of mine,
To Thy bosom I would flee;
I am not my own but Thine;
God be merciful to me.

verses.yoruba:
O pẹ ta ti de ẹmi mi
Sinsin l'o kun ẹwọn ẹsẹ;
Oju Rẹ tan 'mọlẹ iye,
Mo taji, tubu si 'mọlẹ;
Ẹwọn mi bọ, mo d'om'nira
Mo dide, mo si ntọ lẹyin.

verses.english:
Lift ye then your voices;
Swell the mighty flood;
Louder still and louder
Praise the precious blood.

verses.yoruba:
O ti ka b'a ti fade ẹgun
De ori Rẹ fun ọ;
'Gbat'O gbadura pe,
'Dariji wọn;
Wọn se laimọkan sa nij'.

verses.english:
When He comes, our glorious King,
All His ransomed home to bring;
Then a new this song we 'Il sing;
Hallelujah! When a Saviour!

verses.yoruba:
Ọlọrun Olufẹ, kinla!
Ẹni aiku ti 'ku fun mi
Ọmọ ayeraye Baba
Ru gbogb' ẹsẹ mi lor' igi;
Ẹni aiku ti ku fun mi;
Oluwa mi, l'a kan mọ 'gi.

A kan mọ 'gi fun gbogbo wa
K'ale pada t'Ọlọrun lọ;
Ẹ gba otọ ẹri na gbọ,
Pe, ẹjẹ Jesu ti ra yin,
Lọdọ Rẹ l'a nri 'dariji;
Oluwa mi l'a kan mọ 'gi.

verses.english:
Amazing grace! How sweet the sound!
That saved a wretch like me;
I once was lost, but now am found;
Was blind, but now I see.

He ever lives above,
For me to intercede;
His all redeeming love,
His precious blood to plead;
His blood atoned for all our race,
And sprinkles now the throne of grace.

verses.yoruba:
Krist' Oluwa ji loni;
Aleluya!
Ẹda at' Angẹli nwi;
Aleluya!
Gb'ayọ at' isẹgun ga;
Aleluya!
K'ọrun at'aye gberin,
Aleluya!

chorus.english:
Let it come, O Lord we pray thee!
Let the shower of blessing fall;
We are waiting, we are waiting;
Oh receive the hearts of all!

verses.yoruba:
Aleluya, Aleluya!
Ogo ni fun Ọlọrun;
Halleluya f'Olugbala,
Ẹnit'O ṣẹgun iku;
Halleluya f'Ẹmi Mimọ,
Orisun 'fẹ wa mimọ;
Aleluya, Aleluya,
F'Ọlọrun Mẹtalọkan.

verses.english:
I know that my Redeemer lives;
What comfort this sweet sentence gives!,
He lives!, He lives, Who once was dead;
He lives, my everlasting Head.

He lives, my kind, wise, constant friend;
Who still will keep me to the end;
He lives, and while He lives I'll sing,
Jesus, my Prophet, Priest, and King.

verses.yoruba:
O mbẹ lati pese aye,
Y'O si mu mi de be l'ayọ;
O mbe, ogo f'orukọ Rẹ;
Jesu ọkan na titi lae.

verses.english:
He lives, and grants me daily breath;
He lives, and I shall conquer death;
What joy and blest assurance gives!
I know that my, Redeemer lives!

Lord, be mine this prize to win
Guide me through a world of sin;
Keep me by Thy saving grace;
Give me at Thy side a place,
Sun and shield alike Thou art;
Guide and guard my erring heart,
Grace and glory flow from Thee;
Shower, O shower them, Lord on me!

verses.yoruba:
Baba, jẹ ki njere bẹ;
S'amọna mi l'aye yi;
F'ore-ọfẹ pa mi mọ;
Fun mi l'aye l'ọdọ Rẹ;
Iwọ l'ọrun, at'asa;
To ọkan isina mi,
Iwọ l'orisun ore,
Rọ ojo Rẹ s'ori mi.

verses.english:
'The Lord is risen indeed';
The grave has lost his prey;
With him is risen the ransomed seed
To reign in endless day.

verses.yoruba:
'Wọ Oluwa iye, O wa tọ 'ku wo;
Lati f'ipa Rẹ han, O sun ni 'boji;
Wa, Ẹni Olotọ, Si m'ọrọ Rẹ sẹ,
Ọjọ kẹta Rẹ de, jinde Oluwa!

verses.english:
Loose the souls, long prison'd,
bound with satan's chain;
All that now is fallen raise to life again;
Show Thy face in brightness, bid the nations see;
Bring again our daylight; day returns with Thee.

The strife is o'er the battle done;
The victory of life is won;
The song of triumph has begun,
Alleluia!

verses.yoruba:
Gbogbo ipa n'iku ti lọ;
Sugbon Kristi f'ogun rẹ ka:
Aiye! Ẹ ho iho ayọ;
Aleluya!

verses.english:
Come and He will give you rest;
Trust him for His word is plain;
He will take the sinfulest,
Christ receiveth sinful men.

verses.yoruba:
Ọkan mi; 'wọ yo se lọ
Kuro lọd'ọrẹ yi,
Sa sunmọ timọtimọ;
Ba gbe titi d'opin;
O se; ailera mi pọ,
Mo kun f'ẹsẹ pupọ
N'tor' emi ko le sako;
Lẹhin mo ba pada.

chorus.yoruba:
Wa, wa s'ọdọ mi;
Wa, wa s'ọdọ mi;
Alarẹ'ọrun nwọ;
Wa, wa s'ọdọ mi

verses.english:
And now, O Lord, give all with us today,
The grace to join our song;
And from the heart to gladly with us say;
'I will to Christ belong!'

verses.yoruba:
Wa, ọkan t'ẹru ẹsẹ npa;
Alan l'Oluwa;
Oun yo si fun Ọ n'isimi
Bi o ba gbẹkẹle.

Bẹni, Jesu l'ọtọ, l'ọna,
Yo f'isimi fun ọ;
Gb'ẹkẹ rẹ le, ma jafara;
'Wọ o ri 'bukun gba.

verses.english:
Jesus, my Lord, to Thee I cry;
Unless Thou help me, I must die;
Oh, bring Thy free salvation nigh,
And take me as I am.

verses.yoruba:
Mo s'ailokun, ẹbi mi pọ;
O ta 'jẹ Rẹ silẹ fun mi;
O le se mi b'O ba ti fẹ,
Gba mi bi mo ti ri.

Ko si hun ti mo le se,
Nko le duro ti' 'pinnu mi;
Sibe, gba mi n'tori okọ Rẹ;
Gba mi bi mo ti ri.

Wo mi, mo wolẹ l'ẹsẹ Rẹ;
Se mi b'O ti tọ loju Rẹ;
Se isẹ Rẹ l'ase pari,
Gba mi bi mo ti ri.

Krist' Olubukun ti fun wa;
Ọrọ 'yanu t'iye;
Ẹlẹsẹ gbọ 'pe ifẹ na,
Ọrọ 'yanu t'iye;
L'ọfọ la fi fun wa
O si ntọ wa s'ọrun.

verses.english:
Once I fought to conquer sin,
While it reigned my soul within;
Till my Saviour came one day;
Then He triumphed over all,
When He heard my pleading call,
And He took my sins away.

Are you struggling for the right,
Jesus has the pow'r and might;
He will help you conquer sin;
He will take its pow'r away,
He will come with you to stay
And will give you peace within.

verses.yoruba:
Gb'ọpagun 'hinrere ga,
Ẹ ma sẹgun nso;
Pe ogun esu nija;
Ho ye f'ẹgbẹ Daniẹl.

chorus.yoruba:
Se gẹgẹ bi Daniẹl;
Ma wo ẹnikan;
Ni ero rere l'ọkan,
Si jẹ ki aye mọ.

verses.english:
To every one whom God shall call
The promise is securely made;
To you far off-He calls you all;
Believe the word which Christ hath said.

verses.yoruba:
B'iro iji lile
Wa kun nu ile yi;
Mi Ẹmi isọkan si wa,
Ọkan kan, imọ kan;
Fun ewe at'agba
L'ọgbọn at'oke wa;
Fi ọkan gbigbona fun wa
Ka yin, ka gbadura.

Awa pejọ s'iwaju Rẹ
Lati kede 'gbala kikun;
Lati jẹwọ ore ta gba,
Nipa Orukọ la Jesu;
Tẹwọ gb'ọpe wa, Oluwa
Tẹ ongbe ọkan wa lọrun.

verses.english:
We wait-according to Thy Word,
Lord, let it to Thy servants be;
May nothing-self, pride prejudice,
Or unbelief-still hinder thee;
Bless'd Spirit, have unhindered way,
In yielded hearts and lives to-day.

verses.yoruba:
Alejo kan ma nkankun
Pe wọle,
O ti pẹ to ti npara;
Pe wọle,
Pe wọle ki o to lọ;
Pe wọle, Ẹmi Mimọ;
Jesu Krist' Ọmọ Baba,
Pe wọle.

verses.english:
Open now to Him your heart
Let Him in;
If you wait He will depart;
Let Him in;
Let Him in, He is your Friend,
He your soul will sure de-fend,
He will keep you to the end,
Let Him in.

Spirit divine, attend our prayers;
Make a lost world Thy home;
Descend with all Thy gracious pow'rs
O come, great Spirit, come.

I am so glad that our Father in heaven
Tell of His love in the Book He has given;
Wonderful things in the Bible I see;
This is the dearest, that Jesus loves me.

Jesus loves me, and I know I love Him;
Love brought Him down my poor soul to redeem;
Yes, it was love made Him die on the tree,
Oh, I am certain that Jesus loves me.

Jesus, we lift our souls to Thee;
Thy Holy Spirit breathe;
And let these little infants be
Baptized into Thy death.

Oh let Thine unction on them rest;
Thy grace their souls renew;
And write within their tender breast
Thy name and nature too.

verses.yoruba:
Lọ tẹle Olugbala yin;
Ẹ f'oju igbagbọ ri;
A! Ọrun si, Ẹmi Baba
Si nke lat' oke wipe,
'Awọn wonyi
Ni ayanfẹ ọmọ Mi'.

verses.english:
We shall reach our home in heaven by and by;
Keep close to Jesus all the way;
Where to those we love we'll never say goodbye,
Keep close to Jesus all the way.

chorus.english:
For they that wait upon the Lord
Shall renew their strength;
They shall mount up with wings
They shall mount up with wings as eagles,
They shah run and not be weary
They shall walk and not faint;
They shall run and not be weary
They shall walk and not faint;
They shall run and not be weary
Shall walk and not faint.

verses.english:
Jesus, I will trust Thee, trust Thee, with my soul;
Guilty, lost, and helpless, Thou canst make me whole,
There is none in heaven or on earth like Thee;
Thou hast died for sinners-therefore Lord, for me.

Jesus, I do trust Thee, trust with doubt,
Whosoever cometh, Thou wilt not cast out;
Faithful is Thy promise, precious is Thy blood;
These my soul's salvation, Thou my Saviour God.

It is glory when the shadows fall to know that He is near;
Oh, what joy to simply trust and pray!
It is glory to abide in Him when skies above are clear;
Yes, with Him, it's glory all the way!

verses.yoruba:
Ma ṣiṣẹ lọ, mase ro pe,
A ko gb'adura ẹdun rẹ;
Ọjo isimi mbo kankan;
Sa rọju duro, mase kun!

verses.english:
My soul draws nigh and cleaves to Thee;
Then let or earth or hell assail,
Thy mighty hand shall set me free;
For whom Thou say'st, he ne'er shall fail.

verses.yoruba:
Ẹyin ero, ẹ sọ fun ni,
Ti 'reti ti ẹyin ni?
Asọ mimọ, ade ogo,
Ni Jesu y'o fi fun wa;
Omi iye la o ma mu;
A o ba Ọlọrun wa gbe,
A o ba Ọlọrun wa gbe,
N'ilẹ mimọ didara;
A o ba Ọlọrun wa gbe
N'ilẹ mimọ didara.

Wo ọpọ ogun ti mbọ wa;
Esu nko wọn bọ;
Awọn alagbara nṣubu,
A fẹ damu tan!

Tirẹ, titi lae l'awa se;
A Para wa fun Ọ;
Titi aye ainipẹkun
Amin, bẹni k'o ri.

Gba 'fẹ mi, fi ṣe Tirẹ;
Ki o tun jẹ t'emi mọ;
Gb'ọkan mi, Tirẹ n'iṣe
Ma gunwa nibẹ titi.

verses.english:
Work for the night is coming, work through the morning hours;
Work while the dew is sparkling, work mid springing flow'rs;
Work, when the day grows brighter, work in the glowing sun;
Work, for the night is coming, when man's work is done.

verses.yoruba:
Ṣiṣẹ 'tori oru mbọ! ṣiṣẹ li owurọ;
Ṣiṣẹ nigbat' iri nsẹ; ṣiṣẹ n'nu tanna;
Ṣiṣẹ ki ọsan t'o pọn, ṣiṣẹ nigb'orun nran;
Ṣiṣẹ 'tori oru mbọ! 'gba 'ṣẹ o pari.

verses.english:
Work, for the night is coming, work through the sunny noon;
Fill brightest hours with labour, rest comes sure and soon;
Give every flying minute something to keep in store;
Work, for the night is coming, when man works no more.

verses.yoruba:
Ṣiṣẹ 'tori oru mbọ! Ṣiṣẹ l'osan gangan;
F'akoko rere fun 'se, isimi daju;
F'olukuluku igba ni nkan lati pamọ;
Ṣiṣẹ 'tori oru mbọ! 'gba 'sẹ o pari.

verses.english:
Work, for the night is coming, under the sunset skies;
While their bright tints are glowing, work, for daylight flies;
Work, till the last beam fadeth, fadeth to shine no more;
Work while the night is dark'ning, when man's work is o'er.

verses.yoruba:
Ṣiṣẹ 'tori oru mbọ! Ṣiṣẹ l'oju ale;
Ṣiṣẹ 'gbat' imọlẹ wa, ọjọ bu lọ tan;
Ṣiṣẹ titi de opin, ṣiṣẹ titi d'alẹ;
Ṣiṣẹ 'gbat' ilẹ ba nsu, 'gba'ṣẹ o pari.

verses.english:
To the work, to the work! We are servants of God;
Let us follow the path that our Master has trod
With the balm of His counsel our strength to renew;
Let us do with our might what our hands find to do.

To the work, to the work! let the hungry be fed,
To the fountain of life, let the weary be led;
In the cross and its banner our glory shall be;
While we herald the tidings,
'Salvation is free'.

verses.yoruba:
Ao ṣiṣẹ! Ao ṣiṣẹ! Gbogbo wa ni y'o se,
Ijọba okunkun at'isina y'o fo;
A o si gbe orukọ Jehofa l'eke,
N'nu orin yin wa pe;
'Ọfẹ n'igbala'.

verses.english:
At the sign of triumph satan's legions flee;
On then, Christian soldiers, on to victory!
Hell's foundations quiver, at the shout of praise;
Brothers, lift your voices, loud your anthems raise.

Crowns and thrones may perish, kingdoms rise and wane,
But the Church of Jesus Constant will remain;
Gates of hell can never 'gainst that Church prevail;
We have Christ's own promise, and that cannot fail.

verses.yoruba:
Jesu npe wa kuro ninu
Ohun aye asan yi;
Larin afẹ aye O nwi;
Pe: 'Kristian, ẹ fẹran Mi'.

verses.english:
Dismiss me not Thy service, Lord,
But train me for Thy will;
For even I, in fields so broad,
Some duties may fulfil;
And I will ask for no reward,
Except to serve Thee still.

verses.yoruba:
Jesu ma yọ mi n'nu sẹ Rẹ,
To mi fun ifẹ Rẹ;
N'tor' emi ko le sairise
L'oko titobi yi;
Emi ko ni bere oya
Ki nsa ma sin Ọ si.

verses.english:
How many serve, how many more
May to the service come;
To tend the vines, the grapes to store
Thou dost appoint for some;
Thou hast Thy young men at the war
Thy little ones at home.

verses.yoruba:
Ọpọ ni awọn ti nsin Ọ,
Aye wa f'ọpọ si;
Iṣẹ itọju ajara
L'O yan f'awọn miran;
Awọn akoni mbẹ l'ogun
Ọmọde mbẹ n'ilẹ.

verses.english:
All works are good, and each is best
As most it pleases Thee;
Each worker pleases when the rest
He serves in charity;
And neither man nor work unblest
Wilt Thou permit to be.

verses.yoruba:
Gbogbo iṣẹ li o dara,
B'o ba sa ti wu Ọ;
Bi oṣiṣẹ nf'ifẹ jọsin,
Iṣẹ rẹ y'o wu Ọ;
'Wọ ki o sai bukun Iṣẹ
At'oṣiṣẹ pẹlu.

verses.english:
Our Master all the work hath done
He asks of us to-day;
Sharing His service, every one
Share too His Sonship may;
Lord, I would serve and be a son;
Dismiss me not, I pray.

verses.yoruba:
Jesu ti ṣe iru Iṣẹ;
T'On ni k'a se loni,
Ẹni ba ni 'pin n'nu 'ṣẹ Rẹ;
Y'o ba jogun pẹlu;
Uno ṣiṣẹ ki nle j'omo Rẹ;
Jọwọ mase yo mi.

Jesu mo fẹ Ọ, mo mọ P'O jẹ temi,
Mo f'aye ẹsẹ silẹ nitori Rẹ;
Iwọ l'Olugbala, Olurapada;
Bi nko fẹ Ọ tẹlẹ, n'siyi mo fẹ Ọ.

Ni iye tabi ni kiku un o fẹ Ọ,
Un o fi gbogbo ọjọ aye mi yin Ọ;
Nigba iku un o si kọ orin yi pe;
Bi nko fẹ Ọ tẹlẹ, n'siyi mo fẹ Ọ.

Mo fi gbogbo rẹ fun Jesu,
Mo mọ p'Ẹmi ba le mi;
A! ayọ igbala kikun;
Ogo, ogo, f'okọ Rẹ.

Tẹsiwaju, ere daju;
Laipẹ ao ri ẹwa Rẹ;
Ao silẹkun ita wura,
N'biti ao ma gbe titi.

Kristian mase jafara;
Gbọ b'angẹli rẹ ti nwi;
Ni arin ọta lo wa,
Ma sọra.

verses.english:
Gird thy heavenly armour on;
Wear it ever, night and day;
Ambushed lies the evil one:
Watch and pray.

verses.yoruba:
Wọ 'hamọra ọrun rẹ,
Wọ l'ọsan ati l'oru;
Esu ba, ọ nd'ọdẹ rẹ;
Ma sọra.

Gbọ b'Oluwa rẹ ti wi,
Eni ti iwo fẹran;
F'ọrọ Rẹ si ọkan rẹ;
Ma sọra.

verses.english:
Watch, as if on that alone
Hung the issued of the day;
Pray, that help may be sent down;
Watch and pray.

verses.yoruba:
Gba to ba dabi pe adura ko gba
Ko gbagbe ẹbẹ atọkan Rẹ wa;
Duro se pẹlẹ gbẹkẹle ọrọ Rẹ;
Gba A gbọ yoo da ọ lohun.

Gba A gbọ 'nu 'banujẹ atirora;
Ọkan Rẹ kaanu fun ọ nigba yii;
Ko gbogbo aniyan Rẹ le Oluwa;
Ko gbogbo wọn sabẹ 'ṣẹ Rẹ.

Gb'Ọlọrun gbọ bi 'jakulẹ tilẹ wa;
Gb'Ọlọrun gbọ li o pese fun ọ;
Yoo wa titi gbogbo Jọba le parun;
Ijọba Rẹ wa titi lae.

chorus.english:
Have faith in God, He's on the throne;
Have faith in God, He watcheth o'er His own,
He cannot fail, He must prevail;
Have faith in God, have faith in God.

chorus.yoruba:
Gb'Ọlọrun gbọ O wa n'tẹ Rẹ,
O nso awọn agbo to jẹ Tirẹ;
Ko le kuna, O ti bori;
Gb'Ọlọrun gbọ, gb'Ọlọrun gbọ.

verses.yoruba:
Ẹda ko le sọ kikoro ago,
T'Olugbala mu k'ẹlẹsẹ le ye;
Aye Rẹ tilẹ buru ju temi lọ;
Jesu ha le jiya, kemi si ma sa?

verses.english:
Through the love of God our Saviour,
All will be well;
Free and changeless is His favour,
All, all is well;
Precious is the blood that heal'd us;
Perfect is the grace that seal'd us;
Strong the hand stretch'd forth to shield us,
All must be well.

verses.yoruba:
Nipa ifẹ Olugbala,
Ki y'o sí nkan;
Oju rere Rẹ ki pada
Ki y'o sí nkan;
Ọwọn l'ẹjẹ t'o wo wa san;
Pipe ledidi or'ọfẹ;
Agbara l'ọwọ t'o gba ni,
Ko le si nkan.

verses.english:
Thou we pass through tribulation,
All will be well;
Christ hath purchas'd full salvation,
All, all is well;
Happy still in God confiding;
Fruitful, if in Christ abiding;
Holy, through the Spirit's guiding,
All must be well.

We expect a bright tomorrow;
All, will be well;
Faith can sing through days of sorrow,
All, all is well;
On our Father's love relying,
Jesus every need supplying,
Then in living or in dying
All must be well.

verses.yoruba:
Fun mi n'igbagbọ to le sọ
Oke giga di pẹtẹlẹ;
Fun mi ni ifẹ adura,
Ti nfẹ lati tun 'le Rẹ kọ;
K'ifẹ Rẹ bori ọkan mi,
Ko si gba gbogb' ẹmi mi kan.

Idanwo ati iyemeji
At'ewu ko le ba ni l'ẹru;
'Tori mo di ileri yi mu;
'Ore-ọfẹ Mi to fun ọ'.

Ẹkun ko le gba mi,
Bi mo le f'ẹkun wẹ 'ju;
Ko le mu ẹru mi tan,
Ko le wẹ ẹsẹ mi nu;
Ẹkun ko le gba mi.

Ma kegbe buburu, ma sọrọ Ibi,
Mase pe orukọ Ọlọrun l'asan;
Jẹ ẹni ti nronu at'olotitọ;
Sa tẹjumọ Jesu, y'O mu o la ja.

Akoko nkọja lo laifọta pe;
A f'ọjọ kan sunmọle wa si;
Onidajọ mbọ, gọngọ yi o sọ;
Awawi kan kosi l'ọjọ na.

Duro d'Oluwa, ma ṣiyemeji,
Ohunkohun t'o wu ko le de;
'Gbat'o ro p'o pin 'ranwọ Rẹ y'o de;
Ẹni 'yanu l'Ọba Oluwa.

chorus.yoruba:
Ah! ko je gbagbe wa;
Ah! ko je gbagbe wa;
Ṣugbọn Jesu ko jẹ gbagbe wa.

verses.english:
Give to the winds thy fears;
Hope, and be undismayed,
God hears thy sighs, and counts thy tear;
God shall lift up thy head.

verses.yoruba:
F'ẹru rẹ f'afẹfẹ;
N'ireti, ma foya;
Ọlọrun gbọ 'mikanlẹ rẹ;
Y'o gbe ori rẹ ga.

verses.english:
Precious, precious blood of Jesus
Shed on Calvary;
Shed for rebe's, shed for sinners;
Shed for thee!

Precious, precious blood of Jesus;
Let it make thee whole;
Let it flow in mighty cleansing;
O'er my soul.

verses.yoruba:
Ẹjẹ Jesu iyebiye;
Jẹ ko wo ọ san;
Orisun iwẹnumọ
Fọkan rẹ.

verses.english:
Though thy sins are red like crimson
Deep in scarlet glow;
Jesus' precious blood shall wash three;
White as snow.

verses.yoruba:
B'ẹsẹ rẹ pọn bi ododo;
Tabi alaari;
Ẹjẹ yo wẹ ọ mọ
Rekete.

Ẹjẹ ta fi ra wa pada;
O san 'gbese wa;
O fun wa ni idariji
Alafia.

chorus.yoruba:
Ẹjẹ Jesu iyebiye;
Tinsan titi lae;
Gbagbọ, si we nin'ẹjẹ naa,
Fun ọ ni.

verses.yoruba:
L'aifoya l'apa Jesu,
Mo bọ lọw' aniyan;
Mo bọ lọwọ idanwo,
Ẹsẹ ko nipa mọ;
Mo bọ lọwọ 'banujẹ,
Mo bọ lọwọ ẹru;
O ku idanwo diẹ,
O k'omije diẹ.

O gbe gbogbo 'banujẹ at'irora mi ru,
O jodi agbara mi n'igba 'danwo;
'Tori Rẹ mo k'ohun gbogbo ti mo ti fẹ sílẹ,
O sí f'agbara rẹ gbé ọkàn mi ro;
Bí ayé  tilẹ̀ kọ mi, ti Satani dàn mi wo,
Jesu yo mu mi d'opin irin mi;

verses.english:
'Tis so sweet to trust in Jesus,
Just to take Him at His word;
Just to rest upon His promise;
Just to know, 'Thus saith the Lord'.

Holy Bible, book divine,
Precious treasure, thou art mine;
Mine, to tell me whence I came;
Mine, to teach me what I am.

Mine, to chide me when I rove;
Mine, to show a Saviour's, love;
Mine, art thou to guide my feet;
Mine, to judge, condemn, acquit.

Master, speak! Thy servant heareth,
Waiting for Thy gracious word
Longing for Thy voice that cheereth;
Master! Let it now be heard.
I am list'ning, Lord, for thee;
What hast Thou to say to me?

verses.yoruba:
Ma wi, 'tori 'ranṣẹ Rẹ gbọ,
Mo duro de ọrọ Rẹ;
Mo fẹ gb'ohun iwosan Rẹ;
Jẹ k'emi gbọ, Oluwa,
Kristi, mo t'ẹti silẹ
S'ohun t'o fẹ wi fun mi.

Ma wi, pe mi, Oluwa mi
Jẹ ki nle mọ ohun Rẹ;
Ma wi, ki nyara tẹ le Ọ,
Kin sun mọ Ọ girigiri
Nibit' O ntọ agbo Rẹ;
Labẹ ibi itura.

verses.english:
Master, speak! Though least and lowest,
Let me not unheard depart;
Master, speak! For o Thou knowest
All the yearning of my heart,
Knowest all its truest need;
Speak! And make me blest indeed.

verses.yoruba:
Ba ni sọ Oluwa,
Ọrọ Rẹ ti a nsọ;
Jẹki ẹkọ wa jẹ
Gẹgẹbi ọrọ Rẹ;
K'awọn agutan Rẹ
Le ma mo hun Rẹ;
Ibit'O ntọ wọn si
Ki wọn si le ma yọ.

verses.english:
Live Thou within us, Lord;
Thy mind and will be ours;
Be Thou belov'd, adored,
And served, with all our pow'rs;
That so our lives may teach
Thy children what Thou art,
And plead, by more than speech,
For Thee with every heart.

verses.yoruba:
B'Ọlọrun Ọba ọrun
Ti ma nsọrọ n'igba ni;
O tun ba wa sọrọ bẹ loni,
Arakunrin otọ ni
Ohun t'O ba wi fun ọ;
Ohun kan l'aigbọdọ-mase, gbọran.

verses.english:
Wonderful Bible! Book of God;
Guide and counsel to mortals giv'n;
Lamp to the path by the ransomed trod,
Lighting the way from earth to heav'n.

Rising to sing my Saviour's praise,
Thee may I publish all day long;
And let Thy precious word of grace
Flow from my heart and fill my tongue;
Fill all my life with purest love,
And join me to the Church above.

Cling to the Bible, tho' all else be taken;
Lose not its precepts so precious and pure;
Souls that are sleeping its tidings awaken;
Life from the dead in its promises sure.

Cling to the Bible! This jewel and treasure,
Brings life eternal, and saves fallen man;
Surely its value no mortal can measure;
Seek for its blessing, O soul, while you can!

verses.yoruba:
Di Bibeli mu, 'sura 'yebiye ni;
O nf'iye anipẹkun f'araye;
Ko si ẹda na to le wọn iye rẹ;
Wa ibukun rẹ nigba to le ri.

verses.english:
Lo, He comes with clouds descending,
Once for favour'd sinners slain;
Thousand thousand saints attending
Swell the triumph of His train;
Hallelujah!
God appears on earth to reign.

Yea, Amen; let all adore Thee,
High on Thine eternal throne;
Saviour, take the pow'r and glory;
Claim the kingdom for Thine own,
Oh come quickly,
Everlasting God, come down.

At his call the dead awaken,
Rise to life from earth and sea;
All the pow rs of nature, shaken,
At his call prepare to flee;
Careless sinner, careless sinner,
What will then become of thee?

Rejoice, the Lord is King!
Your Lord and King adore;
Mortals, give thanks, and sing,
And triumph evermore;
Lift up your heart, lift up your voice;
Rejoice; again I say, Rejoice.

Jesus the Saviour reigns,
The God of truth and love;
When He had purg'd our stains,
He took His seat above,
Lift up your heart, lift up your voice;
Rejoice; again I say, Rejoice.

verses.yoruba:
Iwọ mbọ wa, Oluwa;
Iwọ mbọ wa, Ọba mi;
Ninu 'tansan ẹwa Rẹ,
Ni titayọ ogo Rẹ.

chorus.yoruba:
Ọlọrun y'O tọ ọ;
Lojojumọ, l'ọna gbogbo;
Oun y'O ma tọju rẹ,
Ọlọrun y'O tọ ọ.

verses.english:
Peace, doubting heart! My God's I am;
Who formed me man, forbids my fear;
The Lord hath called me by my name,
The Lord protects, for ever near;
His blood for me did once atone;
And still He loves and guards His own.

verses.yoruba:
Mase bẹru 'wọ ọkan mi;
Ẹlẹda mi ni nma foya;
Oluwa pe mi l'orukọ,
O ndabobo, ko si jinna
Ẹjẹ Rẹ ti s'etu fun mi.
O nfẹ, o si ntọ mi sibẹ.

'Gba mo nkọja larin ibu,
Mo f'igbagbo tọrọ 'ranwo
Igbi si duro l'okere
Wọn bi kuro li ori mi;
Emi ko bẹru ipa wọn;
Ko si ewu, Ọlọrun mbẹ.

Olugbala, duro ti mi;
Dabobo mi nigba 'danwo,
Pa mi mọ ni ikawọ Rẹ,
F'agbara 'gbala han n'nu mi;
Ki apa Rẹ jẹ abo mi,
Ko s'ohun le ja mi kuro.

Aṣẹgun ati ajogun ni a jẹ,
Nipa ẹjẹ Kristi a ni ìṣẹgun;
B'Oluwa jẹ tiwa, a kì yo ṣubu;
Ko s'ohun to le bori agbara Rẹ.

chorus.yoruba:
Aṣẹgun ni wa, nipa ẹjẹ Jesu;
Baba fún wa nì 'ṣegun, nipa ẹjẹ Jesu;
Ẹni t'apa fẹlẹsẹ
Sibẹ, O wa, O njọ́ba;
Awa ju aṣẹgun lọ,
Awa ju aṣẹgun lọ.

verses.yoruba:
Ẹru 'ji ko ba mi, won yoo dekun;
'Danwo ko le pa mi, 'tori mo l'alafia;
Gbogb'ohun ti mo kọ silẹ, nko fẹ mọ,
Uno r'ohun to ju wọn lọ ni Kenan'.

Wahala ko ni pa, ko le duro pẹ;
Wọn le wa yi mi ka, Uno sa s'ọdọ Jesu;
Gbogb'aye le daru, Ko si mi titi;
Ko si iji ni ebute Kenan'.

N'nu ọpọ ore-ọfẹ, emi fẹ wa
Li abẹ ojiji ti Kenan' ti o pe;
Gbogbo 'gbẹkẹle mi le yẹ, ko jẹ nkan;
Ko s'ohun to le se mi ni Kenan'.

chorus.yoruba:
Awọn to fẹ le duro n'Egypt,
Emi nlọ si Kenan',
Nibi wara at'oyin, yoo tẹ wa l'ọrun;
Lẹhin ajaṣẹgun, ayọ at'alafia jẹ temi;
Ọkan mi yo simi l'ebute Rẹ.

verses.yoruba:
Nigba ti ọna mi ba sokun,
Ti ọjọ ibi ba si de;
 Emi nranti ileri yi pe;
On ko jẹ gbagbe Tirẹ.

verses.english:
Master, with anguish of spirit
I bow in my grief today;
The depths of my sad heart are troubled;
Oh, waken and save, I pray!
Torrents of sin and of anguish
Sweep o'er my sinking soul;
And I perish! I perish! Dear Master,
Oh hasten, and take control.

Master, the terror is over,
The elements sweetly rest;
Earth's sun in the calm lake is mirrored,
And heaven's within my breast;
Linger, O blessed Redeemer,
Leave me alone no more;
And with joy I shall make the blest harbour,
And rest on the blissful shore.

Be joyful, for He is the Lord,
On earth and in heaven supreme;
He fashions and rules by His word;
The 'Mighty' and 'Strong' to redeem.

chorus.english:
Simply trusting day by day,
Trusting Jesus all the way;
Doubting not what'er befall;
Trusting Jesus, that is all.

verses.english:
Singing, if my way be clear;
Praying, if the path be clear;
If in danger, for Him call;
Trusting Jesus, that is all.

verses.yoruba:
Jesu l'ọrẹ to dara julọ,
'Gbati 'gbi aye ba yi lu ọ;
Y'O wo ọkan to gbọgbẹ,
Y'O si fi agbara fun;
Jesu l'ọrẹ to dara julọ.

Wa, awa mbẹ ọ, wa;
Wa, ye gb'oke gb'odo;
Wa mura fun ile,
Mase jafara.

A rán mi ni'ṣe ayọ,
Aleluya!
Un ọ j'iṣẹ na fún ọ ọrẹ mi;
Iṣẹ lat' oke wa ni;
Aleluyah!
Jésù sọ, mo mọ pé otọ ni.

Pada, asako s'ile rẹ;
Were ni, b'o ba pẹ,
Ko si 'dariji n'iboji;
Ọjọ anu kuru;
Pada, pada.

chorus.english:
That means you, brother, that means you;
Trust the Saviour's promise tried and true (my brother)
That means you, brother, that means you;
Whosoe'er believeth that means you.

verses.english:
Today the Saviour calls;
Ye wand'rers, come;
Oh, ye benighted souls,
Why longer roam?

Today the Saviour calls;
For refuge fly;
The storm of justice falls,
And death is nigh.

chorus.yoruba:
Iro didun l'orin Seraf'
Orukọ didun li ahọn;
Orin to dun julọ ni;
Jesu, Jesu, Jesu.

verses.english:
Till He come Oh, let the words
Linger on the trembling chords;
Let the little while between 
In their golden light be seen;
Let us think how Heav'n and home
Lie beyond that till He come!

verses.yoruba:
K'On to de, jẹ k'ọrọ yi
Ma dun titi l'eti rẹ;
Jẹ ki sa die t'o ku
Han gbangba daju fun ọ;
Ronu b'ọrun on ilẹ
Ti d'ẹhin gbat'O ba de.

verses.english:
I hunger and I thirst;
Jesus, my manna be;
Ye living waters, burst,
Out of the rock for me.

Thy truth unchanged hath ever stood;
Thou savest those that on Thee call;
To them that seek Thee Thou art
Sophie that find Thee, all in all.

O Jesus, ever with us stay;
Make all our moments calm and bright;
Chase the dark night of sin away;
Shed o'er the world Thy holy light.

Rescue the perishing, duty demand sit;
Strength for thy labour the Lord will provide:
Back to the narrow way patiently win them;
Tell the poor wand'rer a Saviour had died.

verses.yoruba:
Sọra! L'aṣẹ Jesu;
B'a ti nsọ, ko jina;
B'o ba kuku ti kan 'lẹkun
Ki ẹ si fun logan.

Mo fẹ ki ndabi Jesu
Ninu iṣẹ rere;
K'a le wi nipa t'emi pe;
'O se 'wọn t'o le se'.

verses.english:
Therefore hasten we to Thee;
Take the pledge we bring, O take him;
Let us here Thy glory see,
And in tender pity make him,
Now Thy child, and leave him never
Thine on earth, and Thine forever.

Now upon Thy heart it lies,
What our hearts so dearly treasure;
Heaven ward lead our burdened sighs;
Pour Thy blessing without measure;
Write the name we now have given,
Write it in the book of heaven.

verses.yoruba:
O wu mi ki ndabi Rẹ;
Fun mi l'ọkan igbọran;
'Wọ Alanu, Olore,
Fọkan ifẹ Rẹ fun mi.

verses.english:
Jesus is our Shepherd: well we know His voice,
How its gentlest whisper makes our heart rejoice;
Even when He chideth, tender is His tone;
None but He shall guide us; we are His alone.

Jesus is our Shepherd, for the sheep He bled;
Every lamb is sprinkled with the blood He shed;
Then on each He seateth His own secret sign;
They that have My Spirit, these said He, are Mine.

verses.yoruba:
Jesu fẹ mi En' t'O ku
Lati si ọrun silẹ;
Yio wẹ ẹsẹ mi nu;
Jẹ ki ọmọ Rẹ wolẹ.

Olugbala wa seun;
T'O tẹwọgba 'wọn 'mọ na;
Sugbọn ọpọ ewe mbẹ ti
Ko gbọ okọ Rẹ ri;
Ti wọn ko ka Bibeli ri,
Nibit' Olugbala sọ pe;
Jẹ ki awọn ọmọ-wẹwẹ tọ Mi wa.

Ọre kan mbẹ fun ọmọde
Loke ọrun lọhun;
Ọrẹ tiki yi pada,
T'ifẹ Rẹ ko le ku;
Ko dabi ọrẹ aye
Ti mbajẹ l'ọdọdun;
Ọrẹ yi yẹ lati jẹ
Orukọ Rẹ ọwọn.

Ile kan mbẹ fun ọmọde
Loke ọrun lọhun;
Nibiti Jesu njọba
Ile alafia!
Ko s'ile to jọ l'aye
T'ale fi s'akawe;
Ara rọ 'lukuluku;
Irora na d'opin.

Ẹwu kan mbẹ fun ọmọde
Loke ọrun lọhun;
Harpu olohun didun!
Imọ 'pẹ iṣẹgun;
Gbogbo ẹbun rere yi
La ni ninu Jesu;
Ẹ wa ẹyin ọmọde,
Ki wọn le jẹ ti yin.

Simi le Oluwa-Ẹ gbọ,
Orin duru ọrun;
Simi le 'fẹ Rẹ ailopin;
Si duro jẹ.

Baba, Ẹlẹda gbogbo,
Ninu ọgbọn Rẹ nla;
Lo so awọn meji pọ
Ninu ọgba Edẹni;
Fifun awọn 'mọ Rẹ yi;
Ifẹ atọrun wà,
K'ibukun wa n'ile wọn,
Ile t'Ọlọrun ngbe.

B'Iwọ ko kọ ile na,
Wahala asan ni;
B'Iwọ ko si n'ile wọn,
Asan ni ayọ wọn;
Sugbọn ile t'Iwọ wa
Idapọ didun ni;
'Bit' ifẹ Rẹ ba wa;
Ifẹ ailopin ni.

Ba wa pe, Immanuel;
Si so ọwọ wọn pọ;
B'ẹda meji ti papọ
L'ara ijinlẹ Rẹ.

Ba wa pe, Ẹmi Mimọ;
F'ibukun Rẹ fun wọn;
Si ṣe wọn ni asepe
Gẹgẹ b'O ti ma nṣe.

Oluwa, f'asẹ Rẹ si
Idapo t'a njẹri yi;
F'ola Rẹ ba wa pejọ,
F'ileri 'fẹ wọn mulẹ;
Sọ 'dapọ yi di mimọ
Fun wọn ati lọdọ Rẹ.

A ko fẹ iṣẹ yanu,
Pe ki omi di waini;
Gbogbo ifẹ ọkan wa
Ni, k'a to ifẹ Rẹ wo;
K'agbara lat'oke wa
Sọ 'fẹ aye di mimọ.

verses.english:
We ourselves are God's own field,
Fruit unto His praise to yield;
Wheat and tares together sown,
Unto joy or sorrow grown;
First the blade, and then the ear,
Then the full corn shall appear;
Grant, O harvest Lord, that we
Wholesome grain and pure may be.

For the Lord our God shall come,
And shall take His harvest home;
From His field shall in that day
All offences purge away;
Give His angels charge at last
In the fire the tares to cast;
But the fruitful ears to store
In His garner evermore.

verses.yoruba:
N'tori Ọlọrun wa mbọ
Y'o si kore Rẹ silẹ;
On o gbọn gbogbo panti
Kuro l'oko rẹ njọna;
Y'O f'ase f'awọn angẹl'
Lati gba epo s'ina;
Lati ko Alikama
Si aba Rẹ titi lae.

verses.english:
Lord of the harvest, Thee we hail;
Thine ancient promise doth not fail
The varying seasons haste their round,
With goodness all our years are crown'd,
Our thanks we pay This holy day;
Oh let our hearts in tune be found.

verses.yoruba:
Oluwa 'kore, 'Wọ l'a yin;
Ileri Rẹ 'gbani ko yẹ
Orisi igba si nyipo,
Ọdọdun kun fun ore Rẹ;
L'ọjọ oni, awa dupẹ,
Jẹ kiyin gba ọkan wa kan.

verses.english:
If spring doth wake the song of mirth;
If summer warms the fruitful earth;
When winter sweeps the naked plain,
Or autumn yields is ripen'd grain,
Still do we sing to Thee, our King;
Through all their changes thou dost reign.

verses.yoruba:
B'akoko 'rugbin mu wa yọ;
B'igba ẹrun nmu oru wa;
'Gba t'ọwọ ọjọ ba nrinlẹ;
Tab' igbati 'kore ba pọn,
'Wọ Ọba wa l'a o ma yin;
'Wọ l'alakoso gbogbo wọn.

verses.english:
Lord of harvest, all is Thine:
The rains that fall, the suns that shine,
The seed once hidden in the ground
The skill that makes our fruits abound;
New every year Thy gifts appear;
New praises from our lips shall sound.

verses.yoruba:
Oluwa 'kore, Tirẹ ni
Ojo ti nrọ, orun ti nran;
Irugbin ti a ngbin silẹ,
Tirẹ l'ọgbọn ti nmu dagba;
Ọtun l'ẹbun Rẹ l'ọdọdun;
Ọtun n'iyin Rẹ l'ẹnu wa.

verses.english:
He only is the Maker
Of all things near and far;
He paints the wayside flower,
He lights the evening star;
The winds and waves obey Him,
By Him the birds are fed;
Much more to us, His children,
He gives our daily bread.

verses.yoruba:
On nikan li Ẹlẹda
Ọrun ati aye;
O fun itanna l'ẹwa,
O mu irawọ tan;
Iji gba ohun Rẹ gbọ,
O mbọ awọn ẹyẹ;
Paapaa awa ọmọ Rẹ
L'O mbọ lojojumọ.

verses.english:
Christ is our corner stone,
On Him alone we build;
With His true saints alone
The courts of Heaven are filled;
On His great love our hopes we place,
Of present grace and joys above.

Oh, then with hymns of praise
These hallow'd courts shall ring:
Our voices we will raise;
The three in one to sing;
And thus proclaim in joyful song,
Both loud and long, that glorious name.

Christ is the foundation of the house we raise;
Be its walls salvation, and its gateways praise;
May its threshold lowly to the Lord be dear;
May the hearts be holy that shall worship here.

verses.yoruba:
Kristi ni ipilẹ Ile t'a nkọ yi;
K'odi rẹ jẹ 'gbala k'ọna rẹ jẹ 'yin,
Ki iloro sọwọn l'oju Oluwa;
K'ọkan awọn ti nsin nihin jẹ mimọ.

Nihin ni k'Ẹmi Rẹ ma gbọ ẹjẹ wa;
K'alaisan r'iwosan, k'a m'asako bọ;
K'onirobinujẹ ri 'dariji gba;
K'awọn t'o ti pinya tun ni irepọ.

verses.english:
Here may every token of Thy presence be;
Here may chains be broken, prisoners here set free;
Here may light illumine every soul of Thine,
Lifting up the human into the divine.

verses.yoruba:
K'Ọlọrun sọ ọ k'a tun pade!
Ki imọran Rẹ gbe ọ ro;
K'o ka ọ mọ agutan Rẹ;
K'Ọlọrun sọ ọ k'a tun pade!

chorus.yoruba:
Jesu y'o pẹlu rẹ,
Jesu y'o pẹlu rẹ,
Y'o jẹ ọrẹ at'olutunu fun ọ;
Jesu y'o pẹlu rẹ, Jesu pẹlu rẹ;
Jesu y'o pẹlu rẹ de opin.

verses.yoruba:
Itanna didun wa n'bẹ,
N'ile didan yi;
Awọn ọmọde nkọ
Orin yin Jesu;
A! B'orin na ti dun to;
Wọn y'itẹ funfun na ka;
Nigbawo ni uno ri ọ,
Ile didan, didan yi?

verses.english:
The golden evening brightens in the west;
Soon, soon to faithful warriors cometh rest;
Sweet is the calm of paradise the blest,
Alleluia!

But lo! There breaks a yet more glorious day;
The saints triumphant rise in bright array;
The King of Glory passes on His way,
Alleluia!

The saints of God! Their conflict past,
And life's long battle won at last,
No more they need the shield or sword;
They cast them down before their Lord;
O happy saints! For ever blest;
At Jesus feet how safe their rest!

The saints of God their vigil keep,
While yet their mortal bodies sleep,
Till from the dust they too shall rise
And soar triumphant to the skies;
O happy saints! Rejoice and sing;
He quickly comes, our Lord and King.

There's land of peace and plenty, and its gates are open wide,
And the pure in heart and holy, in its shelter may abide;
It is not thro' gates of glory that a soul must enter in;
But all who would find entrance there must leave the ways of sin.

verses.yoruba:
A nsọrọ ita wura Rẹ;
Ọsọ odi rẹ ti ko l'ẹgbẹ,
'Faji rẹ ko se f'ẹnu sọ;
Y'o ti dun to lati de 'bẹ!

verses.english:
Soon we'll reach the crystal river;
Soon our pilgrimage will cease;
Soon our golden harp strings quiver
With the melody of peace.

Sleep on, beloved, sleep and take thy rest;
Lay down thy head upon thy Saviour's breast;
We love thee well; but Jesus loves thee best,
Goodnight! Good-night! Good-night!

Calm is thy slumber as an infant's sleep;
But thou shalt wake no more to toil and weep;
Thine is a perfect rest, secure and deep,
Goodnight! Good-night! Good-night!

verses.yoruba:
'Ranṣẹ Ọlọrun, seun',
Simi n'nu lala rẹ;
Iwọ ti ja, o si ṣẹgun;
'Bọ s'ayọ Baba rẹ',
Ohun na de loru,
O dide lati gbọ;
Ọfa iku si wọ l'ara,
O subu, ko bẹru.

A! Otutu ki mu wọn,
Loke ọrun; loke ọrun;
Ọwọ re wọn ti kọja,
Gbogbo ọjọ l'o dara;
Loke ọrun; loke ọrun.

Ẹgbẹgbẹrun aimoye
Wọn wọ asọ ala;
Ogun awọn t'a rapada,
Wọn kun 'bi 'mọlẹ na;
Ija wọn pẹlu ẹsẹ
At'iku ti pari;
Ẹ s'ilẹkun wura silẹ
Fun awọn aṣẹgun.

verses.english:
Bring near Thy great salvation,
Thou Lamb for sinners slain;
Fill up the roll of Thine elect,
Then take Thy power and reigns;
Appear, Desire of nations
Thine exiles long for home;
Show in the heav'n Thy promised sign;
Thou Prince and Saviour, come.

chorus.english:
Count me with the children of the heavenly king;
Count me with the servants who would service bring;
Count me with the ransomed who his praises sing;
Count me, count me.

verses.yoruba:
Baba, niwaju itẹ Rẹ;
L'angẹli ntẹriba;
Nigbagbogbo niwaju Rẹ
Ni wọn kọrin iyin;
Wọn si nfi ade wura wọn
Lelẹ yi 'tẹ na ka;
Wọn nfi ohun pẹlu duru
Kọrin si Oluwa.
